{
  "stem": "14060.8",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The other way, four or five meters away, people got killed because it was really truly the place where the bombs fell.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So even when you are in a camp, you can get killed by bombs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It is a matter of your destiny or your luck.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Anyway, now, as winter approached, for some reason or other, they transferred us in the same area up the hill into another camp, which was opposite the railway station called Reinsdorf.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I've seen that camp being described in Martin Gilbert's book.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It's not-- wasn't one of the well-known camps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It had about 6,000, 7,000 people with the changes taking place, which is being disregarded.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And we were there till February, 1945, when, again, we managed to get back to Buchenwald with an ill transport.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Because by that time, Auschwitz was liberated by the Americans, so they couldn't take anybody back there, and we got back to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Circumstances were terrible by that time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Food was not available.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Dysentery, illness, you name it, you couldn't compare the place to what it was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Food was practically non-existent.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because my father was getting a little bit weak.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He got an infection, and they had to amputate a finger of his.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we felt that he won't be able to work, and it's better if we go back with-- he gets back with an ill transport, because we knew that Buchenwald was a transit camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if he goes, then we want to go as well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we wheedled it out that we got in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But before we were sent back, one interesting event happened-- there's nothing terrible about it-- that on Christmas-New Year period, suddenly they decided one night they take everybody for disinfection.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
